abstract: >-
  Annotation reliability shapes downstream NLP systems, but it is unclear
  how much of the disagreement in labels comes from annotator demographics
  versus from the content itself. This work compares human annotators of
  varied demographics against demographically persona-prompted LLMs, using
  SHAP to attribute label decisions to specific text spans. Across the
  studied tasks, content-driven explanations dominated demographic
  effects: text content was the primary driver of labels, and content-
  aware SHAP guidance was more effective for steering LLM annotators than
  persona prompting.
